results.name: Number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons, C_(3h) symmetry and containing n carbon atoms.
reference: G. Brinkmann, G. Caporossi and P. Hansen, "A Survey and New Results on Computer Enumeration of Polyhex and Fusene Hydrocarbons", J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 43 (2003) pp. 842-851. See Table 5 column 4 on page 847.
example: If n=63 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 1.
If n=66 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 2.
If n=69 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 8.
If n=72 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 21.
If n=90 then the number of benzenoids with 22 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 755.
